comments.body:
PowerShell calls ChangeServiceConfigW and [docs](
https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/api/winsvc/nf-winsvc-changeserviceconfigw) say:
```
If the account name specified by the lpServiceStartName parameter is the name of a managed service account
 or virtual account name, the lpPassword parameter must be NULL.

Passwords are ignored for driver services.
```
So the request could be implemented.

The code is: https://github.com/PowerShell/PowerShell/blob/bfb4a818bf265c63a3951a07467ae0e912265973/src/Microsoft.PowerShell.Commands.Management/commands/management/Service.cs#L1791-L1811

We could test:
```c#
    if (Credential != null)
    {
        username = Credential.UserName;
        if (Credential.Password.Length != 0)
        {
            password = Marshal.SecureStringToCoTaskMemUnicode(Credential.Password);
        }
    }
```
